main event: On 24-26 December 1965, officers on board the cargo vessel SS Marfa observed water turbulence resembling mist or fog in front of the ship.
interesting points: The turbulence had a diameter of approximately 50 feet and extended from the surface to a height of 30-40 feet., The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes before dissipating slowly., No magnetic disturbances or radio reception effects were noted during the event., The sighting was officially entered into Project Blue Book on 6 January 1966., The sighting occurred while the ship was docked in Seattle, Washington.
sighted object: water turbulence resembling mist or fog
witness description: officers on board the cargo vessel SS Marfa
